<paragraph blockId="5.[178,1085,928,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
C o m m e n t: The distribution of this subspecies is confined to Fuerteventura and the small island Los Lobos, 
<collectingRegion box="[436,590,957,979]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[605,744,958,979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" pagination="693 - 712" refId="ref6912" refString="ASSING V. (1999): A revision of the Canarian species of Leptobium CASEY (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 31 (2): 693 - 712." type="journal article" year="1999">ASSING 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[756,811,957,979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 182" refId="ref6949" refString="ASSING V. (2005): A revision of the genus Leptobium CASEY (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), Nr. 673: 1 - 182." type="journal article" year="2005">2005</bibRefCitation>
). Note that in SCHÜLKE &amp; SMETANA (2015), 
<emphasis box="[370,593,987,1008]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="WOLLASTON" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[370,498,987,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricolle">L. nigricolle</taxonomicName>
ruficolle
</emphasis>
is still listed as a distinct species, although its subspecific status had been proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[591,743,1016,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 182" refId="ref6949" refString="ASSING V. (2005): A revision of the genus Leptobium CASEY (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), Nr. 673: 1 - 182." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
